    <section id="dark_section">

        <p>The circular economy is an economic system aimed at eliminating waste and the continual use of resources. It contrasts with the traditional linear economy, which follows a 'take, make, dispose' model. The circular economy seeks to create a closed-loop system, minimizing resource input, waste, emissions, and energy leakage through the design of durable, reusable, and recyclable products. </p>


    </section>


