                Principles of the Circular Economy
            </span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <section id="dark_section">

        <p>The circular economy operates on key principles designed to create a sustainable and efficient system. It focuses on designing out waste and pollution, keeping products and materials in use, and regenerating natural systems. This involves sustainable product design, material efficiency, maintenance, repair, reuse, redistribution, remanufacturing, and recycling. By emphasizing these aspects, the circular economy aims to minimize resource input and waste.</p>
        
    </section>

